<p><strong>Battle Hammer</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Great Hammers" href="/Great+Hammers">Great Hammer (Warhammer)</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Battle Hammer</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for high strength players who can hold this weapon's weight. The weight is worth the ability to crush&nbsp;enemy armor, sometimes along with the enemy itself.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Large iron great hammer designed for gladiatorial combat. Used by duelists who were exiled from the colosseum.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Weighty enough to crush armor and its wearer alike.&nbsp;</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Battle Hammer in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Battle Hammer weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Dropped randomly by hammer-wielding Duelists near the colosseum in&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Leyndell Royal Capital" href="/Leyndell+Royal+Capital">Leyndell Royal Capital</a>, accessible from the West Capital Rampart site of grace.&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>Prior to patch 1.03 was dropped by&nbsp;<a title="Elden Ring Grave Warden Duelist" href="/Grave+Warden+Duelist">Grave Warden Duelist</a>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a title="Elden Ring Murkwater Catacombs" href="/Murkwater+Catacombs">Murkwater Catacombs</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=8101&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=8101&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Interactive Map Link</a>]</li> 
 <li>Can't be farmed after beating <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Maliketh, the Black Blade" href="/Maliketh,+the+Black+Blade">Maliketh, The Black Blade</a> as the Duelists vanish afterwards.</li> 
</ul> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Battle Hammer Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>:&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Braggart's Roar" href="/Braggart's+Roar" target="">Braggart's Roar</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon can be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a> and buffed with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic" target="">Magic</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Battle Hammer</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stones" href="/Smithing+Stones" target="">Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;200</li> 
 <li>Base drop rate is 4% (at 100 Discovery)</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
